  "translations": {
    "en": "It is reported in a narration from al-Sadiq (peace be upon him) that he said: He delayed them until dawn. Ya'qub went to Egypt, and Yusuf went out to receive him. He was about to dismount for Ya'qub, then he remembered his status as king and did not do it. So Gabriel (peace be upon him) descended upon him and said to him: O Yusuf, indeed Allah, Mighty and Majestic, says to you: What prevented you from dismounting for My righteous servant? What were you thinking? Extend your hand. So he extended it, and light came out from between his fingers. He said to him: What is this, O Gabriel? He said: This means that no prophet will ever come from your loins, as punishment for what you did to Ya'qub when you did not dismount for him.",
    "ur": "",
    "tr": "",
    "fa": "",
    "id": "",
    "bn": "",
    "es": "",
    "fr": "",
    "de": "",
    "ru": "",
    "zh": ""
  }
